The paper discusses a message broker system for enabling distributed IoT applications over heterogeneous cloud platforms. This involves topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for dynamic selection and migration of message brokers, which could fall under the category of distributed systems (cs.Distributed Systems). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of cloud compute nodes for near-the-edge data analytics, which could involve topics related to databases (cs.DB).
